obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (34910)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. The word "and" and sub-section (2) rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1914 (10 of 1914), s. 3 and the First Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00012_190310_1523339874358&sectionId=34910&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00012_190310_1523339874358
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Victoria Memorial Act, 1903; ^1***`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (34911)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Trustees.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00012_190310_1523339874358&sectionId=34911&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00012_190310_1523339874358
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Trustees of the Victoria Memorial (hereinafter called the Trustees) shall be`
  line `the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Government of West Bengal, ex officio, Chairman ;`
  line
  line `(b) the Chief Justice of the High Court of West Bengal, ex officio ;`
  line
  line `(c) three persons to be nominated by the Central Government, one of whom shall be a`
  line `representative of commerce and industry, chosen in consultation with the State Government of West`
  line `Bengal and two others chosen from among persons who, in the opinion of the Central Government,`
  line `have expert knowledge of the exhibits in the Victoria Memorial or are museologists, historians or art`
  line historians;
  line
  line `(d) a representative of the Central Government in the Ministry concerned with matters relating to`
  line `the Victoria Memorial, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) a representative of the Central Government in the Ministry of Finance, Department of`
  line `Expenditure, concerned with matters relating to the Victoria Memorial, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) the Mayor of the Corporation of Calcutta and where the Corporation of Calcutta is superseded,`
  line `the Administrator of that Corporation, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(g) an officer, not below the rank of the Accountant General, nominated by the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor General of India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(h) the Secretary to the Government of West Bengal in the Department of Education, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(i) four persons (of whom one at least shall he from the general body of subscribers), to be`
  line `nominated by the Trustees from among persons, who, in the opinion of the Trustees from among`
  line `persons, who, in the opinion of the Victoria Memorial or are museologists, historians or art historians,`
  line `with the approval of the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Trustees shall be a body corporate, with perpetual succession by the name of "The Trustees of`
  line `the Victoria Memorial" and a common seal, and in that name shall sue and be sued, and shall have power`
  line `to acquire and hold property to enter into contracts, and to do all acts necessary for and consistent, with`
  line `the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) All acts done by a majority by those present and voting at a meeting of the Trustees, and all acts`
  line `done in pursuance of a majority decision of the Trustees obtained by circulation to the Trustees of the`
  line `matter requiring decision, shall be deemed to be acts of the Trustees.]`
  line
  line `^3[(3A) If any of the Trustees referred to in clauses (b), (d), (e), (f), (g) and (h) of sub-section (1) is`
  line `unable to attend any meeting of the Trustees, he may, with the previous approval of the Chairman,`
  line `authorise in writing a person to do so.]`
  line
  line `(4) No act of the Trustees shall be, deemed to be invalid merely by reason of any vacancy in, or defect`
  line `in the constitution of the body of the Trustees.`
  line
  line `(5) In the case of ex officio Trustees the person for the time being performing the duties of any of the`
  line `offices mentioned in sub-section (1) shall act as a Trustee.`
  line
  line `(6) The Trustees may appoint a person to act as their Secretary.`
  line
  line `(7) Orders for the payment of money on behalf of the Trustees shall be deemed to be sufficiently`
  line `authenticated if signed by two Trustees and countersigned by the Secretary.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 1981, s. 2, for sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 1943, s. 2, for sub-section (3) (with retrospective effect).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 32 of 1981, s. 2.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (34912)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Property vested in Trustees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00012_190310_1523339874358&sectionId=34912&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00012_190310_1523339874358
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `All sums of money now in the custody of the said Provisional`
  line `Executive Committee and all other property, whether movable or immovable, which have been or may`
  line `hereafter be given, bequeathed or otherwise transferred for the purposes of the said Memorial or acquired`
  line `for the said purposes by the Trustees shall vest in the Trustees.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (34913)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Officers and servants to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00012_190310_1523339874358&sectionId=34913&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00012_190310_1523339874358
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `All Officers and servants employed by the Trustees`
  line `shall be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860):`
  line
  line `Provided that this section shall not apply to persons in the service of any contractor employed by the`
  line Trustees.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (34914)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title Rules.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00012_190310_1523339874358&sectionId=34914&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00012_190310_1523339874358
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government ^1[by notification in the Official Gazette,] may make rules to`
  line `carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line provide--
  line
  line `(a) for the manner in which Trustees, other than ex officio Trustees, shall be appointed, and for the`
  line `periods of time for which such Trustees shall hold office;`
  line
  line `(b) for the manner in which meetings of the Trustees shall be convened, the quorum necessary for`
  line `the transaction of business, and the procedure at such meetings;`
  line
  line `^2[(bb) for the manner in which a majority decision of the Trustees shall be obtained by circulation`
  line `to the Trustees of the matter requiring decision;]`
  line
  line `(c) for the appointment of Committees of the Trustees, and the powers of expenditure and control`
  line `which may be delegated to such Committees;`
  line
  line `(d) for the erection, maintenance .and management of the Memorial, the care and custody of the`
  line `objects deposited therein, and the conditions under which the public shall have access thereto;`
  line
  line `^3[(da) for the fees to be levied for admission to the Victoria Memorial;]`
  line
  line `(e) for the form of accounts to be kept by the Trustees, and for the audit and publication of such`
  line `accounts. ^4***`
  line
  line `^5** * * *`
  line
  line `^6[(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of`
  line `the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 1981, s. 2.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 25 of 1943. s. 3.`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 32 of 1981. s. 3.`
  line
  line `4. The word "and" omitted by s. 3 ibid.`
  line
  line `5. Clause (f) omitted by s. 3 ibid.`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 32 of 1981, s. 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (34915)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power of Trustees to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 4,ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00012_190310_1523339874358&sectionId=34915&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00012_190310_1523339874358
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[6. Power of Trustees to make regulations.--(1) The Trustees may, with the previous approval of`
  line `the Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations, not inconsistent with`
  line `this Act and the rules made thereunder, for enabling the body to discharge its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the conditions and restrictions subject to which articles and things vested in the Trustees may be`
  line `given on loan;`
  line
  line `(b) the recruitment and conditions of service of the employees of the Victoria Memorial.`
  line
  line `(3) Every regulation shall, as soon as may be, after it is made by the Trustees, be forwarded to the`
  line `Central Government and that Government shall cause a copy of the same to be laid before each House of`
  line `Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days, which may be comprised in one session`
  line `or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the`
  line `session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the`
  line `regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that regulation.]`
